The second program takes the first character of that input string and adds 1 to its ASCII value, then prints that character. Wait, but the second program's code is:

s = r.readLine();
System.out.printf("%c", s.charAt(0) + 1); So if the first program outputs "Yes", then the second program takes the first character 'Y' (ASCII 89), adds 1 to get 90, which is 'Z', so output is 'Z'.
